The SwitchPath cat-back system from @awetuningofficial offer two distinct tones in one package. This kit unleashes a signature soundtrack out of the Z06, whether the valves are open or closed, thanks to its specifically tuned straight-through mufflers and precision-engineered x-pipe. It’s aggressive with the valves closed, and viscous with them open–just how a high-revving flat-plane V8 should be. Well-collected and comfortable when cruising (like stock), a riot when ripping, all controlled via the factory controls. If you’re planning on high flow cats, proceed with confidence as we engineered our mufflers to be fully capable of controlling those harsh frequencies. There’s also no need for a post-install visit to your local dealer for a valve relearn. Once it’s on, you’re clear for takeoff. Not only does the SwitchPath feature tier 1 OEM-supplied valves, included in every kit is a set of machined aluminum brackets to accommodate the factory valve motors and their factory linkage, keeping them away from the hot exhaust prolonging the lifespan of the electronics. Further, these valves won’t rattle a year later after installation – others on the market will. Two machined aluminum heat shields bolt-on to the Z06’s bumper using factory mounting points allowing the exhaust to shine through the mesh while protecting the inside of the bumper. No exhaust wraps that will inevitably become waterlogged and cause damage to whatever lies underneath. This exhaust system sheds 15lbs off your car’s weight getting rid of that heavy factory system. Topped off with quad 4.5” double-walled slash-cut tips exclusively in diamond black that fill the Z06’s bumper perfectly without any need for additional filler. The SwitchPath system does not interfere with any factory emissions equipment, so it is 100% emissions friendly, and a lifetime warranty comes standard. 😎

"The Vorsteiner aero kit comprises of 4 components that amplify the visual appearance, providing an upgrade to the BMW M8 platform.⁠
FRONT SPOILER:⁠
Our 2x2 weave, carbon fiber front spoiler enhances the original appearance of the OEM front bumper while providing functional aerodynamic upgrades.⁠
REAR DIFFUSER:⁠

DECKLID SPOILER:⁠

REAR BUMPER EYEBROWS3:⁠

Vorsteiner's carbon fiber parts are produced using a state-of-the-art aerospace autoclave system. This provides unsurpassed rigidity, strength and finish to our aerodynamic components. We distinguish ourselves by utilizing a resin pre-impregnated, vacuum-formed carbon fiber material that results in a 20% - 30% stiffer and stronger product than an equivalent wet-lay up product. ⁠
This technique drastically reduces rejection rates, significantly improving delivery times. Vorsteiner uses a combination of unidirectional, 1x1, and 2x2 weave carbon fiber to keep the weight to a minimum while providing optimum strength and rigidity. The vacuum-formed technology used in our aerodynamic parts draw out excess resin which ultimately draws out excess weight without decreasing structural rigidity. This process provides a much tighter control over the fit and finish giving you the piece of mind that the part will perfectly match the factory shut lines and contours."⁠

You need aftermarket suspension. Here’s why:

1. Responsiveness is paramount to the feel and safety of your ride. High quality components like shocks, control arms, sway bars, etc. can drastically improve handling even over stock suspension. 

2. Going fast is great until you need to stop. People often overlook the role suspension plays in braking. High quality aftermarket suspension can decrease “brake dive” to more evenly distribute the energy throughout the vehicle and not unload the rear end. 

3. Longevity and endurance are greatly increased with aftermarket suspension because of the much higher quality materials used. Like polyurethane bushings instead of the lower grade rubber in most factory systems. 

4. Not only can you get the added look of either lowering or lifting your ride, we can also powder coat components to match other elements on your ride or just express your style better than that boring stock suspension. 

5. There are tons of other benefits that are specific to the application and our sales team can get you up to speed on what will give you the most out of your ride!
